---
source: crates/carta/tests/golden_e2e.rs
expression: output
---
\section{!!!}\label{section}

A heading that slugs to nothing falls back to a reserved identifier.

\section{???}\label{section-1}

Another empty slug is disambiguated against the fallback.

\section{Foo}\label{foo}

A base identifier.

\section{Foo}\label{foo-1}

A repeat gains a numeric suffix.

\section{Foo 1}\label{foo-1-1}

A title that already carries the suffix is disambiguated further.

\section{İ here}\label{i-here}

A dotted capital I lowercases to a letter plus a combining mark that the
identifier drops.

\section{WordͅEnd}\label{wordend}

A letter-like combining mark is not a letter and is dropped from the
identifier.
